com.cyc.baseclient.connection

Interface SublWorkerSynch

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Cancelable, Worker
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultSublWorkerSynch

    public interface SublWorkerSynch
extends Worker

    WorkerSynch is designed to provide a handle for a particular communication event with a Cyc server in a synchronous manner. DefaultWorkerSynch provides the default implementation while Worker and DefaultWorker provide asynchronous communications capabilities. Currently, WorkerSynchs are one-shot, i.e., a new WorkerSynch needs to be created for every new communication. WorkerSynchs are cancelable, time-outable and provide means for incremental return results.

    Example usage: 

     try {
    CycAccess access = CycAccessManager.getAccess();
    WorkerSynch worker = new DefaultWorkerSynch("(+ 1 1)", access);
    Object work = worker.getWork();
    System.out.println("Got worker: " + worker + "\nGot result: " + work + ".");
  } catch (Exception e) {
    e.printStackTrace();
  }

        Object getWork()
        throws CycConnectionException,
               CycTimeOutException,

        This method starts communications with the Cyc server, waits for the work to be performed, then returns the resultant work.
        Returns:
        The work produced by this WorkerSynch
        Throws:
        CycConnectionException - thown when there is a problem with the communications protocol with the CycAddress
        CycTimeOutException - thrown if the worker takes to long to return results
        CycApiException - thrown if any other error occurs
